# Shadcn UI Usage Policy

- **Preference**: Always use existing shadcn/ui components and their related libraries whenever possible.
- **No duplication**: **Do not** create a new UI component if an equivalent already exists.
- **Scope**: This applies to all TypeScript and TSX files under `apps/web`.

## Where to look first
- Existing shared/UI components may live in:
  - `apps/web/src/components`
  - `packages/ui/src/components`
- Shadcn configuration for the web app: [apps/web/components.json](mdc:apps/web/components.json)

## Adding shadcn components (Bun)
Run these from the `apps/web` directory:

```bash
cd apps/web
bunx --bun shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

If shadcn hasn’t been initialized yet, initialize first (non-interactive):

```bash
cd apps/web
bunx --bun shadcn@latest init -y
```

## Guidance
- Prefer shadcn/ui primitives (and related libraries such as `@radix-ui/*`, `class-variance-authority`, or `tailwind-variants`) over custom implementations.
- Before introducing a new component, search for an existing one with the same purpose and reuse/extend it.
- [Shadcn UI Components](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components)
- Use shadcn mcp server to search for components

